  "title": "Engineering Assistant/Technician (Chemical Lab/Semiconductor, 12 hours shifts, East region)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Operate lab equipment for failure analysis, physical characterization, and quality control.</li>\n  <li>Monitor SPC and calibrate IMTE to ensure equipment quality.</li>\n  <li>Follow lab procedures and cleanroom protocols.</li>\n  <li>Meet measurement cycle time and perform timely calibration.</li>\n  <li>Operate equipment according to SOP.</li>\n  <li>Maintain lab cleanliness and order.</li>\n  <li>Assist in special projects assigned by supervisors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Physics, Material Science, or related Engineering field.</li>\n  <li>Preferably 2 years of lab or semiconductor industry experience.</li>\n  <li>Fresh graduates are welcome to apply.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Word and Excel.</li>\n  <li>Experience with SEM/EDX, SRP is an advantage.</li>\n  <li> Willing to work on shifts as needed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>______________________________________________________</strong></p>\n<p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on “Quick Apply” or contact win@hkmsvs.com for more details.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p>\n<p><strong>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</strong></p>\n<p><strong>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>3) Expected salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</strong></p>\n<p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
